data.description: One or more photo(s) has been virtually staged. Price improvement just made on this beautiful property! In the heart of historic Oakland, welcome to the ultimate lakefront living experience with an opportunity to own a beautiful, 4 bedroom, 3 full bath home, on .64 acres, in this quaint town with over 118 feet of waterfront living on Lake Apopka! As you enter the property, when greeted beyond the foyer and 11 foot ceiling line family room, you are immediately swept away with breathtaking views of the 30,000 acre lake, making it the perfect setting for relaxation and entertainment. Imagine yourself enjoying your morning coffee while watching the sunrise on the large 30' x 40' ft deck, with an herb garden and citrus trees close-by, or the oversized dock closer to the water. The lake views are absolutely stunning, with the option to entertain family and friends with a barbecue on the back lawn 16' x 16' covered cabana to also experience the beautiful Florida sunsets. A private boat dock with a Leeson brand lift, measuring 21' x 26', allows immediate lakefront access where you can indulge in your favorite water activities, from wakeboarding, skiing, wake surfing, fishing, body boarding and kayaking, which is ideal for any boater or fishing enthusiast. It's a hidden gem to know that Lake Apopka is part of the Harris Chain of Lakes, which flows through the Apopka-Beauclair Canal with direct access North to the Ocklawah River, which continues through canals and locks that will take you all the way to the Atlantic Ocean in Jacksonville! A new full home 24kw Generac Generator adapting to two 420LP tanks conveys with the property. The oversized garage includes a workshop area. Water Heater and Air Conditioner are within 5 years new. The landscaping on this property is immaculate with a thorough french drain system that handles the irrigation flowing from the lake, which keeps your water bill low. Walking distance to the West Orange Trail and community park with a playground, tennis court and pickle ball court, along with the neighboring Jack Voss Park with its' brand new pier, make this location perfect for your family. It's location is also just a bike or golf cart away to the town schools, and everything fun and beautiful Downtown Winter Garden has to offer, like great restaurants, shops, farmers market, festivals and events! The town is also very close to major interchanges so you’re only 25 min from Downtown Orlando, Disney and Universal! Very low HOA costs, as this is a very small and quaint neighborhood. Don’t miss this rare opportunity and schedule your private showing today!
